ner is running\n615: - [ ] Check container logs\n616: \n617: **Verification**:\n618: ```bash\n619: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n620: sleep 10\n621: docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID\n622: docker logs $CONTAINER_ID\n623: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n624: ```\n625: \n626: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n627: - Container starts successfully\n628: - Container status is \"running\"\n629: - No errors in container logs\n630: - Application is initialized\n631: \n632: ---\n633: \n634: ### Task 32: Test health check\n635: - [ ] Run container in background\n636: - [ ] Wait for health check to run\n637: - [ ] Check container health status\n638: - [ ] Verify health status is \"healthy\"\n639: - [ ] Verify health check is working\n640: \n641: **Verification**:\n642: ```bash\n643: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n644: sleep 30\n645: docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID\n646: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n647: ```\n648: \n649: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n650: - Health check runs\n651: - Health status is \"healthy\"\n652: - Health check interval is 30s\n653: - Health check timeout is 10s\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ### Task 33: Test port exposure\n658: - [ ] Run container with published ports\n659: - [ ] Publish port 8080\n660: - [ ] Publish port 9090\n661: - [ ] Test connectivity to port 8080\n662: - [ ] Test connectivity to port 9090\n663: - [ ] Verify health endpoint is accessible\n664: \n665: **Verification**:\n666: ```bash\n667: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -p 9090:9090 agentcube:latest)\n668: sleep 10\n669: curl -f http://localhost:8080/healthz || echo \"Port 8080 accessible\"\n670: curl -f http://localhost:9090/metrics || echo \"Port 9090 accessible\"\n671: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n672: ```\n673: \n674: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n675: - Port 8080 is accessible\n676: - Port 9090 is accessible\n677: - Health endpoint responds\n678: - Metrics endpoint responds\n679: \n680: ---\n681: \n682: ### Task 34: Verify Dockerfile syntax with linter\n683: - [ ] Install hadolint\n684: - [ ] Run hadolint on Dockerfile\n685: - [ ] Fix any linting errors\n686: - [ ] Fix any linting warnings\n687: - [ ] Verify no critical issues remain\n688: \n689: **Verification**:\n690: ```bash\n691: docker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint < Dockerfile\n692: ```\n693: \n694: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n695: - Hadolint passes without errors\n696: - No critical warnings remain\n697: - Dockerfile follows best practices\n698: \n699: ---\n700: \n701: ### Task 35: Verify Dockerfile layer optimization\n702: - [ ] Inspect Dockerfile layer order\n703: - [ ] Verify stable instructions appear first\n704: - [ ] Verify frequently changing instructions appear last\n705: - [ ] Verify dependency installation is before source code copy\n706: - [ ] Verify commands are combined where possible\n707: \n708: **Verification**:\n709: ```bash\n710: docker history agentcube:latest\n711: ```\n712: \n713: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n714: - Stable base image layers are first\n715: - Dependency layers come before source code\n716: - Related commands are combined\n717: - Layer count is minimized (< 15 layers)\n718: \n719: ---\n720: \n721: ### Task 36: Test build caching\n722: - [ ] Perform initial build and measure time\n723: - [ ] Perform second build without changes\n724: - [ ] Measure cache hit rate\n725: - [ ] Verify second build is faster\n726: - [ ] Verify layers are cached correctly\n727: \n728: **Verification**:\n729: ```bash\n730: time docker build -t agentcube:cache1 . 2>&1 | tee build1.log\n731: time docker build -t agentcube:cache2 . 2>&1 | tee build2.log\n732: grep -i \"cache\" build2.log\n733: ```\n734: \n735: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n736: - Second build is significantly faster\n737: - Cache hit rate > 70%\n738: - Layers are reused where possible\n739: \n740: ---\n741: \n742: ### Task 37: Create build script\n743: - [ ] Create scripts/build.sh\n744: - [ ] Add build arguments handling\n745: - [ ] Add image tagging logic\n746: - [ ] Add version argument\n747: - [ ] Add dry-run option\n748: - [ ] Add multi-architecture build support\n749: - [ ] Make script executable\n750: \n751: **Verification**:\n752: ```bash\n753: test -f scripts/build.sh && echo \"Build script exists\" || echo \"Build script missing\"\n754: test -x scripts/build.sh && echo \"Script executable\" || echo \"Script not executable\"\n755: ```\n756: \n757: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n758: - Build script exists in scripts/ directory\n759: - Script is executable\n760: - Script handles build arguments\n761: - Script supports multiple architectures\n762: \n763: ---\n764: \n765: ### Task 38: Test multi-architecture build\n766: - [ ] Create buildx builder\n767: - [ ] Build for linux/amd64 platform\n768: - [ ] Build for linux/arm64 platform\n769: - [ ] Verify both architectures build successfully\n770: - [ ] Test both images run correctly\n771: - [ ] Clean up buildx builder\n772: \n773: **Verification**:\n774: ```bash\n775: docker buildx create --name agentcube-builder --use\n776: docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64 -t agentcube:amd64 --load .\n777: docker buildx build --platform linux/arm64 -t agentcube:arm64 --load .\n778: docker buildx rm agentcube-builder\n779: ```\n780: \n781: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n782: - linux/amd64 image builds successfully\n783: - linux/arm64 image builds successfully\n784: - Both images run on respective platforms\n785: - Cross-compilation works correctly\n786: \n787: ---\n788: \n789: ### Task 39: Verify image security with vulnerability scan\n790: - [ ] Install trivy\n791: - [ ] Run trivy scan on production image\n792: - [ ] Check for HIGH severity vulnerabilities\n793: - [ ] Check for CRITICAL severity vulnerabilities\n794: - [ ] Document any vulnerabilities found\n795: - [ ] Address any security issues\n796: \n797: **Verification**:\n798: ```bash\n799: docker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n800:   aquasec/trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL agentcube:latest\n801: ```\n802: \n803: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n804: - No CRITICAL vulnerabilities (or documented and accepted)\n805: - No HIGH vulnerabilities (or documented and accepted)\n806: - Vulnerability report is generated\n807: - Security posture is documented\n808: \n809: ---\n810: \n811: ### Task 40: Verify reproducible builds\n812: - [ ] Build image with specific versions\n813: - [ ] Record image digest\n814: - [ ] Build image again with same parameters\n815: - [ ] Compare image digests\n816: - [ ] Verify digests are identical\n817: \n818: **Verification**:\n819: ```bash\n820: DIGEST1=$(docker build --quiet -t agentcube:repro1 .)\n821: DIGEST2=$(docker build --quiet -t agentcube:repro2 .)\n822: echo \"Digest 1: $DIGEST1\"\n823: echo \"Digest 2: $DIGEST2\"\n824: [ \"$DIGEST1\" = \"$DIGEST2\" ] && echo \"Builds are reproducible\" || echo \"Builds differ\"\n825: ```\n826: \n827: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n828: - Both builds produce identical digests\n829: - Builds are deterministic\n830: - No random factors affect build output\n831: \n832: ---\n833: \n834: ### Task 41: Create documentation\n835: - [ ] Create docs/docker.md\n836: - [ ] Document build process\n837: - [ ] Document build arguments\n838: - [ ] Document image variants\n839: - [ ] Provide usage examples\n840: - [ ] Document health check endpoints\n841: - [ ] Document metrics endpoints\n842: \n843: **Verification**:\n844: ```bash\n845: test -f docs/docker.md && echo \"Documentation exists\" || echo \"Documentation missing\"\n846: grep -q \"Build Process\" docs/docker.md && echo \"Build process documented\" || echo \"Build process not documented\"\n847: ```\n848: \n849: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n850: - Documentation file exists\n851: - Build process is documented\n852: - Build arguments are documented\n853: - Usage examples are provided\n854: - API endpoints are documented\n855: \n856: ---\n857: \n858: ### Task 42: Update README.md\n859: - [ ] Update README.md with Docker build section\n860: - [ ] Add quick start instructions\n861: - [ ] Add build examples\n862: - [ ] Add run examples\n863: - [ ] Add multi-architecture build instructions\n864: - [ ] Add troubleshooting section\n865: \n866: **Verification**:\n867: ```bash\n868: grep -q \"Docker\" README.md && echo \"Docker section added\" || echo \"Docker section missing\"\n869: grep -q \"docker build\" README.md && echo \"Build command documented\" || echo \"Build command not documented\"\n870: ```\n871: \n872: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n873: - README.md has Docker build section\n874: - Quick start instructions are provided\n875: - Build examples are included\n876: - Troubleshooting section is added\n877: \n878: ---\n879: \n880: ### Task 43: Create .dockerfile documentation\n881: - [ ] Add comments to Dockerfile explaining each stage\n882: - [ ] Add comments explaining complex build steps\n883: - [ ] Add comments for non-obvious COPY commands\n884: - [ ] Add comments explaining optimization techniques\n885: - [ ] Ensure comments are clear and helpful\n886: \n887: **Verification**:\n888: ```bash\n889: grep -q \"# Stage 1: Builder\" Dockerfile && echo \"Builder stage commented\" || echo \"Builder stage not commented\"\n890: grep -q \"# Multi-stage build\" Dockerfile && echo \"Multi-stage explained\" || echo \"Multi-stage not explained\"\n891: ```\n892: \n893: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n894: - Each stage has a descriptive comment\n895: - Complex steps have explanatory comments\n896: - Optimization techniques are documented\n897: - Comments are clear and helpful\n898: \n899: ---\n900: \n901: ### Task 44: Verify build context size\n902: - [ ] Measure build context size\n903: - [ ] Verify .dockerignore is effective\n904: - [ ] Verify unnecessary files are excluded\n905: - [ ] Document build context size\n906: - [ ] Optimize if size is too large\n907: \n908: **Verification**:\n909: ```bash\n910: docker build --progress=plain -t agentcube:context . 2>&1 | grep -i \"context size\"\n911: ```\n912: \n913: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n914: - Build context size is reasonable (< 100 MB)\n915: - Unnecessary files are excluded\n916: - .dockerignore is effective\n917: - Build context size is documented\n918: \n919: ---\n920: \n921: ### Task 45: Final integration test\n922: - [ ] Perform complete build pipeline\n923: - [ ] Build all three image variants\n924: - [ ] Run all three images\n925: - [ ] Verify all functionality works\n926: - [ ] Run all tests\n927: - [ ] Verify no errors\n928: - [ ] Document results\n929: \n930: **Verification**:\n931: ```bash\n932: docker build -t agentcube:latest .\n933: docker build --target builder -t agentcube:dev .\n934: docker build --target verifier -t agentcube:test .\n935: docker images | grep agentcube\n936: ```\n937: \n938: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n939: - All three variants build successfully\n940: - All images run correctly\n941: - All tests pass\n942: - No errors in build or runtime\n943: - Integration test results are documented\n944: \n945: ---\n946: \n947: ## Summary\n948: \n949: **Total Tasks**: 45\n950: **Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 8-12 hours\n951: \n952: ### Key Deliverables\n953: 1. **Multi-stage Dockerfile** with 3 stages (builder, verifier, runtime)\n954: 2. **.dockerignore** file for build context optimization\n955: 3. **Build scripts** for automated builds\n956: 4. **Documentation** (docs/docker.md, README.md updates)\n957: 5. **Testing validation** (unit, integration, security tests)\n958: \n959: ### Success Criteria\n960: - All three Dockerfile stages are implemented correctly\n961: - Multi-stage build produces minimal runtime image (< 250 MB)\n962: - Production image size is at least 50% smaller than builder image\n963: - Non-root user is configured correctly\n964: - Build tools are excluded from production image\n965: - Health checks are configured and working\n966: - All tests pass\n967: - No critical security vulnerabilities\n968: - Multi-architecture builds work correctly\n969: - Documentation is complete\n970: \n971: ### Dependencies\n972: - Docker 20.10+ (for multi-stage build support)\n973: - Go 1.21+ (for building AgentCube components)\n974: - Python 3.11+ (for picod component)\n975: - Base design document: `changes/AR-032/design.md`\n976: - Base specification document: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n977: \n978: ### Blocked By\n979: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n980: \n981: ### Blocks\n982: - AR-033: Controller Manager Deployment (depends on Docker images)\n983: - AR-034: Workload Manager Deployment (depends on Docker images)\n984: - AR-035: Router Deployment (depends on Docker images)\n985: \n986: ### Notes\n987: - Multi-stage builds are critical for security and image size optimization\n988: - Always use specific image versions, never `latest` tag\n989: - Follow Dockerfile best practices for layer optimization\n990: - Run security scans before deploying to production\n991: - Use buildx for multi-architecture builds\n992: - Document any exceptions to security best practices\n\n(End of file - total 992 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Tasks\n\n**Module**: `docker`\n**Language**: Dockerfile\n**Size**: S\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create .dockerignore file\n- [ ] Create .dockerignore file in project root\n- [ ] Add .git directory to exclude\n- [ ] Add *.md files to exclude (README.md, docs/)\n- [ ] Add test files (*_test.go, pytest.ini, .coverage)\n- [ ] Add development files (.vscode/, .idea/, *.swp)\n- [ ] Add build artifacts (dist/, build/, *.exe)\n- [ ] Add CI/CD files (.github/, .gitlab-ci.yml)\n- [ ] Add OS files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db)\n- [ ] Add temporary files (tmp/, temp/, *.tmp)\n- [ ] Add .dockerignore itself to exclude","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775885841621,"end":1775885841654}}}}
